headline: Rouzbeh Yassini-Fard's Gift To The World Connects Its Citizens
summary: Rouzbeh Yassini-Fard, "father of the cable modem," could have made a fortune on his invention. But instead he gave away his breakthrough.

headline: What StandardAero (SARO)'s Raised Guidance and Winnipeg Expansion Means For Shareholders
summary: In the past week, StandardAero reported strong third quarter and nine-month 2025 results with revenue rising to US$1.50 billion and net income up to US$68.12 million, while also raising its full-year revenue guidance and announcing a 70,000 sq. ft. expansion of its Winnipeg engine MRO facility. An additional highlight included StandardAero's delivery of its 1,000th GE Aerospace J85-5 engine to the United States Air Force, underlining its position as a key provider to military and commercial...
